article.headline: Harvard 75, Dartmouth 65
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Siyani Chambers hit all three shots from beyond the arc en route to 22 points and dished out six assists to help Harvard rally and beat Dartmouth 75-65 Saturday in the Ivy League opener for both teams. Wesley Saunders made 8 of 9 shots for 19 points and dished out six assists, Steve Moundou-Missi had 15 points and Laurent Rivard tallied 12 points for Harvard, which shot 62.4 (27 of 43) percent from the field. The Crimson (9-5) have shot 59.7 (83 of 139) percent over their last three games. Dartmouth (3-11) led 62-58 before Chambers and Saunders combined to score each point for Harvard during an 11-1 run that spanned 6 minutes and put the Crimson ahead 69-63. Jvonte Brooks hit two free throws to cut the lead to 69-65, but the Big Green were held scoreless of the final 2:50. Connor Boehm led Dartmouth with 11 points.
